<section>
	<h2 id="other:link">Other usages: link button</h2>
	<p>When no special handlers of the click event are needed â€” just navigation to a certain URL, consider using an
		anchor tag <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> styled as a button. It is achieved by adding a <code class="format-code">.wds-button</code>
		class just like for the <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> element. Optionally add any other desired button classes.
	</p>
	{{#component-demo}}
		{{#wds-button tagName='a' href='#'}}Link button{{/wds-button}}
		{{#wds-button tagName='a' href='#'}}
			{{wds-icon name='fandom-heart' size='small'}}
			<span>Link button</span>
		{{/wds-button}}
		{{#wds-button tagName='a' href='#' class='wds-is-secondary'}}Secondary link button{{/wds-button}}
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>

<section class="button-theming">
	<h2 id="theming">Theming</h2>
	<p>
		Theming can be applied to buttons by <code class="format-code">button-theming</code> mixin.
		For basic usage, mixin takes two parameters: primary-background-color and prmary-text-color:
	</p>
	{{#code-sample language='sass'}}
		.wds-button {
			@include button-theming($wds-color-dark-blue, $wds-color-white);
		}
	{{/code-sample}}

	{{#component-demo}}
		{{#wds-button class='primary-only'}}Primary{{/wds-button}}
		{{#wds-button class='primary-only'}}
			{{wds-icon name='fandom-heart' size='small'}}
			<span>Primary button</span>
		{{/wds-button}}

		{{#wds-dropdown as |dropdown|}}
			{{#dropdown.toggle tagName='button' class='wds-button primary-only'}}
				<span>Dropdown</span>
			{{/dropdown.toggle}}
			{{#dropdown.content}}
				<ul class="wds-list">
					<li>List item 1</li>
					<li>List item 2</li>
					<li>List item 3</li>
				</ul>
			{{/dropdown.content}}
		{{/wds-dropdown}}
		{{#wds-button class='wds-is-secondary primary-only'}}Secondary{{/wds-button}}
		{{#wds-button class='wds-is-text primary-only'}}Text{{/wds-button}}
	{{/component-demo}}

	<p>It is also possible to apply different color for secondary and text buttons than to primary ones:</p>
	{{#code-sample language='sass'}}
		.wds-button {
			@include button-theming($wds-color-slate-gray, $wds-color-white, $wds-color-link);
		}
	{{/code-sample}}

	{{#component-demo}}
		{{#wds-button class='different-secondary'}}Primary{{/wds-button}}
		{{#wds-button class='different-secondary'}}
			{{wds-icon name='fandom-heart' size='small'}}
			<span>Primary button</span>
		{{/wds-button}}

		{{#wds-dropdown as |dropdown|}}
			{{#dropdown.toggle tagName='button' class='wds-button different-secondary'}}
				<span>Dropdown</span>
			{{/dropdown.toggle}}
			{{#dropdown.content}}
				<ul class="wds-list">
					<li>List item 1</li>
					<li>List item 2</li>
					<li>List item 3</li>
				</ul>
			{{/dropdown.content}}
		{{/wds-dropdown}}
		{{#wds-button class='wds-is-secondary different-secondary'}}Secondary{{/wds-button}}
		{{#wds-button class='wds-is-text different-secondary'}}Text{{/wds-button}}
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="group">Button group</h2>
	<p>Group a series of buttons together on a single line with the button group.</p>
	<p>Button group comes with no default styling of its own. Colors, sizes and animations are driven by buttons.</p>
	<p>Wrap a series of buttons with <code>.wds-button</code> in <code>.wds-button-group</code>.</p>
	{{#component-demo}}
		<div class="wds-button-group">
			{{#wds-button}}1{{/wds-button}}
			{{#wds-button}}2{{/wds-button}}
			{{#wds-button disabled=true}}3{{/wds-button}}
			{{#wds-button}}4{{/wds-button}}
			{{#wds-button}}5{{/wds-button}}
		</div>
	{{/component-demo}}
	<p>Mixing primary, secondary and different sizes of buttons is not supported. All buttons have to be of the same type.</p>
	{{#component-demo}}
		<div class="wds-button-group">
			{{#wds-button class='wds-is-secondary'}}6{{/wds-button}}
			{{#wds-button class='wds-is-secondary'}}7{{/wds-button}}
			{{#wds-button disabled=true class='wds-is-secondary'}}8{{/wds-button}}
			{{#wds-button class='wds-is-secondary'}}9{{/wds-button}}
			{{#wds-button class='wds-is-secondary'}}10{{/wds-button}}
		</div>
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>

